><p style="font-weight:normal;text-decoration:none;letter-spacing:0in"
>This form is for use in a civil or family law proceeding in which a party is a minor, a person who lacks legal capacity to make decisions, or a person for whom a conservator has been appointed. A person who seeks the appointment of a guardian ad litem in a proceeding under the Probate Codeâother than a proceeding under Probate Code sections 3500â3613 for approval of a compromise, settlement, or disposition of judgment proceedsâshould use form DE-350/GC-100.<span style="xfa-spacerun:yes"
>Â </span
><span style="font-weight:bold"
>NOTE:<span style="xfa-spacerun:yes"
>Â </span
></span
>A person may not act as a guardian ad litem unless the person is represented by an attorney, is an attorney, or,<span style="xfa-spacerun:yes"
>Â </span
><span style="text-decoration:none"
>in an action under the Uniform Parentage Act (Family Code, Â§Â§Â 7600â7730),</span
> is an adult relative of a minor party.</p
></body
></exData
